  <dataqual>
    <attracc>
      <attraccr>The geologic attributes are combinations of those used
on the original geologic source map. The assumption
was made that the original geologic boundaries were
accurate at a scale of 1:5,000,000, and that the original geologic
attributions on the source map were correct.</attraccr>
    </attracc>
    <logic>The digitized geologic boundaries were overlain on the
geologic source map and checked for errors, and the
errors were corrected in the digital file using ArcEdit.</logic>
    <complete>The geology of the entire continent of South America was
digitized from the source map.  We made several groupings
of geologic units that were present on the source map, but
all original geologic boundaries remain on the digital map.</complete>
    <posacc>
      <horizpa>
        <horizpar>A visual comparison was made between paper
copies of the digital geologic map and the
source map. The horizontal accuracy of the
boundaries should not be considered accurate at
a scale larger than approximately 1:7,500,000.</horizpar>
      </horizpa>
    </posacc>
