      <procstep>
        <procdesc>The geologic boundaries and a series of
latitude-longitude points of the source map were
inked onto a mylar overlay, and the overlay was
scanned at 300 dpi using a large-format scanner
to produce a TIFF image file.  The TIFF was
converted into an Arc Grid, and then into an Arc
Vector coverage.  The coverage was then
transformed into a bipolar-oblique projection.
Approximately 5000 geologic polygons were
attributed with a scheme modified considerably
from that of the source map. The symbols for
the geologic attribution were made from a
standard set developed for the World Energy
Project.</procdesc>
      </procstep>
    </lineage>
